<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Sam Frost is stripping off for a good cause on The All New Monty: Guys and Gals.</p>

<p>And on Friday, the Home and Away star revealed on Channel Seven's The Morning Show how she was able to overcome her body insecurities.</p>

<p>The 31-year-old actress told hosts Larry Emdur and Kylie Gillies that doing the charity burlesque show has helped boost her body confidence.</p>

<p>Body battles: On Friday, Home and Away star Sam Frost (pictured) revealed how she was able to overcome her body insecurities on The All New Monty: Guys and Gals</p>

<p>'I think as females, we all have our own insecurities and it is really daunting to have to strip on TV and then in front of a large crowd,' she said.</p>

<p>'I think one of the biggest things that I was constantly reminded of was why were we doing it and it was breast cancer awareness.</p>

<p>'Any time I would start stressing out or feel insecure or anxious, I would think of the greater picture.'</p>

<p>For a good cause: The 31-year-old actress told The Morning Show hosts Larry Emdur and Kylie Gillies that whenever she felt nervous about showing her body, she would remind herself that the burlesque show was about raising awareness of early detection and prevention of cancer</p>

<p>Sam also credited her co-stars with supporting her during rehearsals and in the lead-up to the live performance.</p>

<p>She said: 'The girls were amazing. We all supported each other and we were all in the same boat, so it was a great sisterhood. That definitely helped me through it.'</p>

<p>Her co-star singer Danielle Spencer, who is Russell Crowe's ex-wife, added: 'There was a lot of support amongst the cast and the crew.'</p>

<p>Support: Sam also credited her co-stars, including singer Danielle Spencer (right), with supporting her during rehearsals and in the lead-up to the live performance</p>

<p>'The girls were amazing': Sam will also perform in the burlesque show alongside beauty queen Erin Holland, entertainer Patti Newton and former Olympian Leisel Jones (cast pictured)</p>

<p>Sam will also perform in the burlesque show alongside beauty queen Erin Holland, entertainer Patti Newton and former Olympian Leisel Jones.</p>

<p>The ladies will be joined on stage by male celebrities, including actor Samuel Johnson, former Home and Away star Orpheus Pledger and comedian Paul Fenech.</p>

<p>The All New Monty: Guys and Gals will see 15 celebrities in total bare all to raise awareness of early detection and prevention of cancer.</p>

<p>The All New Monty: Guys and Gals continues Sunday at 7pm on Channel Seven</p>

<p>Don't miss it: The All New Monty: Guys and Gals continues Sunday at 7pm on Channel Seven </p>
